1k0.title: What is Arbital?
1k0.clickbait: This is the home page for the entire website.
1k0.text:
Like the internet, Arbital is many things to many people. Below is a quick look at what Arbital is and what it can do. Keep in mind, it's still in an alpha version, and discussion is restricted to a few topics and approved users.

At it's core, Arbital is a wiki. It's a place to write, present, and read content. Like Wikipedia, our content will be comprehensive, high quality, and fact-checked. However, we think [1sl we can do 10 times better than Wikipedia]. In part by having content that's better organized, more granular, and specifically tailored to each user. And in part by focusing specifically on figuring out the true answer and recognizing domain-specific expertise.

At this stage, Arbital works great as a tool for explaining complicated topics. In fact, you can think of Arbital as [1sm "Google Maps for knowledge."] The platform can figure out what you know, what you should or want to learn, and then dynamically pick the best content for you to read. It also allows authors to create content that automatically tailors itself to the reader's knowledge and needs. In this area Arbital's capability has already surpassed any existing platform.

In the near future we will also build out Arbital to be the best platform for [1sn discussion], [1sp hosting a blog], and [1sq staying up to date]. While it may seem like Arbital is trying to do many things at once, each feature set is critical for Arbital's mission to become the best platform for all content ranging from cutting-edge science to popular entertainment.
	
*Are you a superprogrammer who wants to solve hard problems and fix online discussion?  Do you understand the vision behind Arbital and have interest to work on it as a product designer?  Are you interested in getting involved with Arbital some other way? Talk to us: alexei@arbital.com.*
